1 (2) A WARRANT OF RESTITUTION UNDER § 8–401 OF THE REAL
2 PROPERTY ARTICLE;
3 (3) AN ACTION FOR WRONGFUL DETAINER UNDER § 14–132 OF THE
4 REAL PROPERTY ARTICLE;
5 (4) A FORECLOSURE ACTION UNDER § 7–105.1 OF THE REAL
6 PROPERTY ARTICLE;
7 (5) A SHERIFF’S SALE UNDER TITLE 11, SUBTITLE 5 OF THE COURTS
8 ARTICLE; AND
9 (6) AN ACTION AGAINST THE PROPERTY OF THE ALLEGED DISABLED
10 PERSON.
11 (B) A STAY UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION MAY REMAIN IN
12 EFFECT UNTIL:
13 (1) THE COURT APPOINTS A TEMPORARY OR PERMANENT GUARDIAN
14 OF THE PROPERTY OF THE DISABLED PERSON, WHICHEVER OCCURS FIRST; OR
15 (2) THE COURT DENIES THE PETITION.
16 (C) (1) TO EFFECTUATE SERVICE OF PROCESS ON AN ALLEGED DISABLED
17 PERSON FOR AN ACTION STAYED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION, THE
18 TEMPORARY OR PERMANENT GUARDIAN OF THE PROPERTY OF THE DISABLED
19 PERSON, AS APPROPRIATE, MUST BE SERVED.
20 (2) AN ACTION STAYED UNDER THIS SECTION MAY BE DISMISSED IF
21 SERVICE OF PROCESS IS NOT EFFECTUATED IN COMPLIANCE WITH PARAGRAPH (1)
22 OF THIS SUBSECTION.
23 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall be construed to
24 apply only prospectively and may not be applied or interpreted to have any effect on or
25 application to any petition for the guardianship of the property of an alleged disabled
26 person filed before the effective date of this Act.
27 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
28 October 1, 2025.

